				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: OoW first thoughts -xping<a name="62064"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 10:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We were in the Wall of Slaughter most of the night.  Mob positioning and all is clearly designed to give monks a leg up as pullers.  Spaced so they always come in pairs, 75% are lull-immune (for now anyway - by this I mean 66+) and pretty magic resistant making a mez-fade tough to rely on even if you can afford the mana to do one every 3 minutes.  XP for the mobs was 2-4% of an AA per kill in a full group in level 66.  Actual XP in 66 is harsh as folks say -- I have mine at 50-50 for another AA at least as I want that 9th song slot.  I got about 9% of the level in two hours of grouping and about half an AA at the same time with XP split 90/10 for the first hour and 50/50 for the second.  Had one death when we tried a red-con named.  Group member insists the mob was one-groupable during beta.  He hit us with an AE 2000 pt DD and feign death proc.  Thing went off about 3 times in 45 seconds.  Nasty action and I was pulling very slowly trying out various tricks.  Was a learning curve.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
